{{refimproveBLP|date=August 2009}}

'''Steve Madge''' is a [[birders|birder]], author, and bird tour leader, based in [[Cornwall]], [[England]].<ref name="Fegely">{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/mcall/access/92490349.html?dids=92490349:92490349&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Feb+19%2C+1989&author=TOM+FEGELY%2C+The+Morning+Call&pub=Morning+Call&desc=EASE+BOREDOM+OF+SNOWLESS+WINTER+WITH+A+NEW+BOOK+FOCUS+ON+NATURE&pqatl=google|title=Ease Boredom of Snowless Winter with a New Book Focus on Nature|last=Fegely|first=Tom|date=19 February 1989|work=[[The Morning Call]]|page=14|accessdate=25 April 2011}}</ref>

He is a former member of the [[British Birds Rarities Committee]]. He is president of the [[Cornwall Birdwatching and Preservation Society]].

He has written three volumes in the [[Helm Identification Guides]] series - on ''Wildfowl'', ''Crows and Jays'' and ''Pheasants, Partridges & Grouse'', and is co-author with [[Mark Beaman]] of [[The Handbook of Bird Identification]].

