{{UK-nonfiction-writer-stub}}

There are two Sydenham Rivers in Ontario.
*The [[Sydenham River (Lake Huron)]] flows north from Williams Lake and falls over the [[Niagara Escarpment]], through the city of [[Owen Sound]] and into [[Georgian Bay]]. *The [[Sydenham River (Lake Saint Clair)]] flows west and south from near [[London, Ontario|London]], emptying into [[Lake St. Clair]] at [[Wallaceburg]].
